Oh man, I, uh, really don't like Meat Circus stuff in general, but once I got past the yuck, I've got two little questions. 1. Why is it assumed to be a Roman Numeral L rather than a letter L? (Is it because the Meat Circus, and presumably this object are Russian, so a Roman Numeral is more plausible in this case than a Latin alphabet L?) 2. Why is there continuing monthly testing of this object? I didn't really get the interest in continuing to see a series of D-class becoming body-horror facepaint art critics, nor did I find their reactions or the object's reactions, to change or escalate in any way that suggested a need for ongoing testing.







